  "text": "Jaulmes and Joux [CITATION_1] were the first to present CCAs against NTRU. Even though their attacks need just a small number of queries to recover f, they do not seem to work for all instantiations of NTRU and require the whole output of the decryption oracle for the recovery of f. In addition, they use invalid ciphertexts of a very special shape and can thus be easily thwarted by a decryption machine (which simply refuses to give an output when the input is an invalid ciphertext).",
